Titolo: Jonah Lomu Rugby

Anno: 1997

Descrizione: Jonah Lomu Rugby is a video game released in 1997. It was developed by Rage Software and published by Codemasters. It was released on DOS, PlayStation and Sega Saturn. Its title is a reference to former All Blacks winger Jonah Lomu.
Following the 2003 closure of Rage Software, several members of the game's development team went on to work on World Championship Rugby.